2749	  (\texttt{Mathlib.Algebra.Category.ModuleCat.Sheaf.Quasicoherent}).}
2750	  A sheaf of modules \(M\) on a scheme is \emph{quasi-coherent}
2751	  (\(\mathrm{IsQuasicoherent}\,M\)) exactly when the type of \emph{quasi-coherence data}
2752	  \(\mathrm{QuasicoherentData}\,M\) is nonempty. A datum
2753	  \(q : \mathrm{QuasicoherentData}\,M\) consists of an index family \(\{X_i\}\) of opens covering the
2754	  whole scheme together with, for each \(i\), a presentation
2755	  \((M.\mathrm{over}\,X_i).\mathrm{Presentation}\) of the restriction of \(M\) to \(X_i\)
2756	  (a cokernel-of-free-modules description on the site over \(X_i\)). Thus quasi-coherence packages a
2757	  cover on which \(M\) is locally presented; on each member of the cover
2758	  \cref{lem:isIso_fromTildeΓ_of_presentation_mathlib} applies.
2759	\end{lemma}
